      "comment": "PRINCE HARRISON (3) was five weeks between runs when he dropped in trip for a fast-finishing sixth over 1200m at Gosford. Proven at this journey and will prove hard to get past here. SILVER TEMPEST (2) blinkers go on fifth-up and he finds a much easier contest today. Not that far away when seventh over 1500m at Hawkesbury with the 59.5kg. Can turn things around. MISCHIEVOUS MOLLY (6) has struggled in five starts on the home track and backs up quickly today. Can push forward and stays in the mix. BRAZIL (1) has not raced since finishing 12th over 1800m at Wagga on April 19. Can sprint well fresh in this class.",
